\[f(x,y,z) = 3x + y + z + |-x + y + z| \ge 3x + y + z + x - (y + z) = 4x.\]But $f(x,y,z) \le 4,$ so $x \le 1.$  This implies that each of $x,$ $y,$ $z$ is at most 1.

